					<h2>Wages and Benefits</h2>
					
					<h3>Benefits</h3>
					
					<h4>Vacation Time</h4>
					
					<p>
						Stop 'n Save offers all its employees paid vacation time.  It is the belief of Stop 'n Save that vacation time is our employees' opportunity to get away from their job responsibilities.  It is a time that is beneficial to the employee, as well as Stop 'n Save, in that it allows the employee to relax and come back to work refreshed.
					</p>
					
					<h4>Health Coverage</h4>
					
					<p>
						Stop 'n Save recognizes the need of employees for financial protection in the event of illness or injuries that result in medical expense and loss of income.  Providing adequate, cost-effective insurance protection is a concern of the company.  The plans selected by Stop 'n Save are designed in an attempt to meet the employees' needs.  Whether you are a part time of full time employee if you work at least an average of 25 hours per week and have been an employee for 6 months you will qualify for health coverage.
					</p>
					
					<h4>401 K Retirement</h4>
					
					<p>
						If you work at least 1000 hours in a year, are 21 years of age and have completed 1 full year of service you may choose to participate in our 401K retirement plan.
					</p>
					
					<h4>Holidays</h4>
					
					<p>
						Stop 'n Save operates on a commitment to service and convenience for its customers.  Employees accept employment with Stop 'n Save fully understanding that they are subject to be scheduled to work on weekends and holiday.  Stop 'n Save employees must realize this commitment to the public is important.  Hourly store level employees will receive time and one-half for hours worked on designated holidays.  Stop 'n Save will observe the following holidays:
					</p>
					
					<ul class="holidays">
						<li>New Years Day</li>
						<li>Memorial Day</li>
						<li>Easter Day</li>
						<li>Labor Day</li>
						<li>Thanksgiving Day</li>
						<li>Christmas Day</li>
					</ul>
					
					<h4>Safety and Security</h4>
					
					<p>
						Stop 'n Save considers its employees to be its most valuable asset and will take every possible measure to make working conditions free from hazard.  It is our intent to continuously facilitate the control, reduction, and elimination of all health and occupational hazards associated with our work activities.  The well-being and safety of our employees and the public is our primary concern and the focus of our safety program.
					</p>
					
					<p>
						Each employee's cooperation is necessary for the safety of your self, fellow employees, and the public.  It is imperative that each employee understands and follows the company's safety rules, instructions, and operating procedures. <strong>Safety is a condition of employment with Stop 'n Save</strong>.
					</p>
					
